open settings -> keymap:

*Select in Project View*: New shortcut: ctrl+shift+2

*Redo* becomes ctrl+y

*Delete Line* becomes ctrl+<

*Comment with line comment* becomes Alt+shift+Dead Grave

# Adding External formatter to be invoked by keypress.


1. Define the command, for example:
/usr/bin/clang-format -i -style=file /home/cyrill/cyrill.gitlab/pytorch_adapter2/ios/Classes/native_opencv.cpp

2. Go To Settings -> Tools -> External Tools, and add the command there
3. Define the shortcut to it: Settings -> Keymap: Search the name you set in step 2.
4. Set your custom keyboard shortcut, for example ctrl + alt + shift + L

